<dl id="n38075c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n38" href="#n38075c">N38 (VI.B.32)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n38all.htm#n38075c"> 75(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Jebusite / (hegoat) <small>Orange</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n38075c"><li>FW 240.28 </li><li><a href="../../flex/kd/lexkd.htm#n38075c">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/kd/l39kd.htm#n38075c">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n38075c">MS BL 47477-75</ms> </li><li>JJA 51:095 <a name="kdd2" href="../../ff/fdra/kda.htm#kdd2">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/kd/kdd2.htm#n38075c">Draft: II.1&sect;4.2</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">&ldquo;I have just come from Jebus,&rdquo; replied Machbonai ben Shuni; &ldquo;but <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> the place teems with wild beasts&mdash;though, for that matter, they are little worse than the people.&rdquo; <br><mark>&ldquo;Jebus?&rdquo; said Ahtur. &ldquo;Isn&apos;t that where the people worship a he-goat?&rdquo;</mark> <br>&ldquo;Quite right,&rdquo; answered Machbonai. &ldquo;They call their city Jerusalem. <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font>&rdquo; &ldquo;To speak frankly,&rdquo; observed the Levite, turning to the giver of the feast; &ldquo;I wondered whether the same deity were not worshipped here in Philistia, and whether it were not in his honour that you had been named Tayish.&rdquo; <br>Tayish and Ahtur broke into a laugh so loud and infectious that the others turned their heads, looked at them with leaden eyes and asked unsteadily what was the matter.<font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> &ldquo;That is nothing but a nickname,&rdquo; said Tayish at last, wiping his eyes. &ldquo;I am not a Philistine. I belong <mark>to the tribe of Dan</mark>.&rdquo; <br>&ldquo;And we have nicknamed him &lsquo;Tayish&rsquo; because of his shock of hair,&rdquo; explained Ahtur, and with a quick movement snatched the cap from his host&apos;s head. A mane of dark-brown hair, extraordinarily thick and fine, fell over his forehead and ears and covered his neck to the shoulders. <small> Vladimir Jabotinsky, <a name="VEJS" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#VEJS"><cite title="source">Samson the Nazarite</cite></a>,(Jan 1930) 19-20</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: The Jebusites were a goat-worshipping Canaanite tribe dispossessed of Jerusalem by David. See also <a name="n34127b" href="n34all.htm#n34127b">N34 (VI.B.27):127(b)</a>. </mm> </dd></dl>
